➝ Clear downward trend driven by technology adoption.

Why Calls Are Dropping
Customers prefer IVR systems, chatbots, and AI agents.
Faster query resolution without waiting for human operators.
Shift in customer behavior → fewer calls, more digital interactions.

📉 Impact on Jobs
Fewer calls → job cuts in traditional call center roles.
Routine tasks increasingly automated.
Human agents needed only for complex, high-value queries.

💡 Impact on Companies
Higher efficiency: reduced workload on human agents.
Cost savings: automation lowers operational expenses.
Profit margins increase due to AI-driven scalability.

Impact on Professionals
Reskilling opportunities in
AI operations
Bot training
Analytics & automation
Human roles evolve toward supervising AI systems and handling escalations.

Broader Implications
AI adoption in call centers mirrors global automation trends.
Efficiency gains for companies vs. displacement risks for workers.
The future of customer support is hybrid: AI-first, human-assisted.


